## Topic 2 — Solving Linear Systems and Gaussian Elimination

A **system of linear equations** can be written as **Ax = b**, where A is a matrix of coefficients, x is the vector of unknowns, and b is the result vector. Solving the system means finding x. The oldest, most fundamental algorithm is **Gaussian elimination** — a sequence of row operations that transforms the system into a simpler form.

**A simple 2×2 system.**

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 2 1)
                              (list 1 3))))
(define b (matrix/make (list (list 5) (list 5))))

(define x (linalg/solve A b))

(list 'A A 'b b 'solution x)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing the 2×2 matrix and solution vector]
<!-- BUILD: run; verify linalg/solve; print result -->

**Check the solution** by computing Ax and comparing to b.

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 2 1)
                              (list 1 3))))
(define b (matrix/make (list (list 5) (list 5))))

(define x (linalg/solve A b))
(define check (matrix/* A x))

(list 'b b 'Ax check 'equal? (matrix/= b check))
```
[VISUAL: text output confirming Ax = b]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**A 3×3 system.**

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 2 3)
                              (list 0 1 4)
                              (list 5 6 0))))
(define b (matrix/make (list (list 14) (list 8) (list 17))))

(define x (linalg/solve A b))

(list 'A A 'b b 'solution x)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing the 3×3 system and solution]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**An inconsistent system** (no solution) — the verb escalates.

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 2)
                              (list 2 4))))
(define b (matrix/make (list (list 3) (list 5))))

(define attempt (linalg/solve A b))

(list 'A A 'b b 'attempt attempt)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing an (escalate ...) result]
<!-- BUILD: run; verify honest-null contract -->

**Underdetermined system** (infinitely many solutions) — also escalates in the current implementation.

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 2 3))))
(define b (matrix/make (list (list 6))))

(define attempt (linalg/solve A b))

(list 'A A 'b b 'attempt attempt)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing an (escalate ...) result]
<!-- BUILD: run; verify escalation on underdetermined system -->

**Larger system — 4×4.**

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 4 1 0 0)
                              (list 1 4 1 0)
                              (list 0 1 4 1)
                              (list 0 0 1 4))))
(define b (matrix/make (list (list 5) (list 6) (list 6) (list 5))))

(define x (linalg/solve A b))

(list 'solution x)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing the 4×1 solution vector]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

