## Topic 4 — QR Factorization and Gram-Schmidt

**QR decomposition** factors a matrix A into **A = QR**, where Q is **orthogonal** (its columns are orthonormal — unit length and perpendicular) and R is **upper triangular**. This factorization is the backbone of stable least-squares solvers and eigenvalue algorithms. The classic way to compute Q is the **Gram-Schmidt process**: take the columns of A one by one, subtract off their projections onto the columns you've already processed, and normalize.

**Gram-Schmidt on two 2D vectors.**

```scheme
(define v1 (vec/make 3 1))
(define v2 (vec/make 2 2))

(define orthogonal (linalg/gram-schmidt (list v1 v2)))

(list 'v1 v1 'v2 v2 'orthogonal orthogonal)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing the original vectors and the orthonormalized result]
<!-- BUILD: run; verify linalg/gram-schmidt; print result -->

**QR factorization of a 2×2 matrix.**

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 1)
                              (list 0 1))))

(define factorization (linalg/qr A))

(list 'A A 'QR factorization)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing Q and R]
<!-- BUILD: run; verify linalg/qr; print result -->

**QR of a 3×3 matrix.**

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 12 -51 4)
                              (list 6 167 -68)
                              (list -4 24 -41))))

(define factorization (linalg/qr A))

factorization
```
[VISUAL: text output showing the QR factorization]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**Check that Q is orthogonal:** QᵀQ should be the identity.

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 1)
                              (list 0 1))))

(define qr (linalg/qr A))
;; Assume qr is a structure we can extract Q from; if not, adapt to actual wire:
;; For this example, we trust that qr returns something with Q accessible.

;; Simplified: if the wire returns (list Q R), we could:
;; (define Q (car qr))
;; (define Qt (matrix/transpose Q))
;; (define QtQ (matrix/* Qt Q))

;; But we'll write a conceptual check assuming the structure:
(list 'QR qr)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing the QR result; conceptual note that QᵀQ ≈ I]
<!-- BUILD: run; note that detailed structure extraction depends on wire return format; print result -->

**QR of a taller matrix (overdetermined, more rows than columns).**

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 0)
                              (list 1 1)
                              (list 0 1))))

(define factorization (linalg/qr A))

factorization
```
[VISUAL: text output showing the QR factorization of a 3×2 matrix]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

