## Topic 5 — Least Squares and Overdetermined Systems

When a system Ax = b has **more equations than unknowns** (tall matrix), there's usually no exact solution — the equations are **overdetermined**. Instead, we find the **least-squares solution**: the x that minimizes the sum of squared residuals ||Ax - b||². Geometrically, it's the projection of b onto the column space of A. Algebraically, it's the solution to the **normal equations** AᵀAx = Aᵀb, or (more stably) via QR.

**Fit a line to three points** — a classic least-squares problem.

```scheme
;; Points: (0,1), (1,2), (2,4)
;; We want to fit y = mx + c, i.e. find m and c.
;; The system is:
;;   c + 0*m = 1
;;   c + 1*m = 2
;;   c + 2*m = 4
;; In matrix form: A*[c; m] = b

(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 0)
                              (list 1 1)
                              (list 1 2))))
(define b (matrix/make (list (list 1) (list 2) (list 4))))

(define x (linalg/least-squares A b))

(list 'A A 'b b 'least-squares-solution x)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing the coefficient matrix and the best-fit [c; m]]
<!-- BUILD: run; verify linalg/least-squares; print result -->

**Check the residuals** — how far off is the fit?

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 0)
                              (list 1 1)
                              (list 1 2))))
(define b (matrix/make (list (list 1) (list 2) (list 4))))

(define x (linalg/least-squares A b))
(define fitted (matrix/* A x))
(define residual (matrix/- b fitted))

(list 'b b 'fitted fitted 'residual residual)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing the original b, the fitted values, and the residuals]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**Fit a line to more points.**

```scheme
;; Points: (0,1), (1,3), (2,2), (3,4)
;; Fit y = mx + c

(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 0)
                              (list 1 1)
                              (list 1 2)
                              (list 1 3))))
(define b (matrix/make (list (list 1) (list 3) (list 2) (list 4))))

(define x (linalg/least-squares A b))

(list 'least-squares-solution x)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing the best-fit [c; m]]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**Fit a parabola (quadratic)** — y = a + bx + cx².

```scheme
;; Points: (0,1), (1,2), (2,5), (3,10)
;; Model: y = a + bx + cx²

(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 0 0)
                              (list 1 1 1)
                              (list 1 2 4)
                              (list 1 3 9))))
(define b (matrix/make (list (list 1) (list 2) (list 5) (list 10))))

(define x (linalg/least-squares A b))

(list 'coefficients x)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing [a; b; c] for the best-fit parabola]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**Larger least-squares problem** — fit a cubic to noisy data.

```scheme
;; Points: (0,1.1), (1,2.0), (2,4.9), (3,9.1), (4,16.0), (5,24.9)
;; Model: y = a + bx + cx² + dx³

(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 0 0 0)
                              (list 1 1 1 1)
                              (list 1 2 4 8)
                              (list 1 3 9 27)
                              (list 1 4 16 64)
                              (list 1 5 25 125))))
(define b (matrix/make (list (list 1.1) (list 2.0) (list 4.9) (list 9.1) (list 16.0) (list 24.9))))

(define x (linalg/least-squares A b))

(list 'cubic-coefficients x)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing [a; b; c; d]]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

