## Topic 6 — Rank and Nullspace

The **rank** of a matrix is the dimension of its column space — the number of linearly independent columns (or rows). A matrix with full rank (rank = min(rows, cols)) has no redundancy; a rank-deficient matrix has dependencies. The **nullspace** (or kernel) of A is the set of all vectors x such that Ax = 0. Its dimension is **nullity**, and the **rank-nullity theorem** says: rank + nullity = number of columns.

**Rank of a full-rank 2×2 matrix.**

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 2)
                              (list 3 4))))

(define r (linalg/rank A))

(list 'A A 'rank r)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing rank = 2]
<!-- BUILD: run; verify linalg/rank; print result -->

**Rank of a rank-deficient 2×2 matrix** (second row is a multiple of the first).

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 2)
                              (list 2 4))))

(define r (linalg/rank A))

(list 'A A 'rank r)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing rank = 1]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**Rank of a 3×3 matrix with one redundant row.**

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 2 3)
                              (list 2 4 6)
                              (list 1 1 1))))

(define r (linalg/rank A))

(list 'A A 'rank r)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing rank = 2]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**Nullspace of a rank-deficient matrix.**

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 2)
                              (list 2 4))))

(define null (linalg/null-space A))

(list 'A A 'null-space null)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing a basis vector for the nullspace]
<!-- BUILD: run; verify linalg/null-space; print result -->

**Nullspace of a full-rank matrix** (only the zero vector).

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 0)
                              (list 0 1))))

(define null (linalg/null-space A))

(list 'A A 'null-space null)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing an empty or trivial nullspace]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**Rank and nullspace of a 3×4 matrix** (underdetermined).

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 2 3 4)
                              (list 2 4 6 8)
                              (list 1 1 1 1))))

(define r (linalg/rank A))
(define null (linalg/null-space A))

(list 'A A 'rank r 'null-space null)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing rank < 4 and a nontrivial nullspace]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

