## Topic 8 — Symmetric Matrices and Orthogonal Diagonalization

A **symmetric matrix** (A = Aᵀ) has special properties: its eigenvalues are always real, and its eigenvectors (from different eigenvalues) are orthogonal. This means a symmetric matrix can be **orthogonally diagonalized**: A = QΛQᵀ, where Q is orthogonal and Λ is diagonal. This is the foundation of principal component analysis, quadratic forms, and many optimization algorithms.

**Check if a matrix is symmetric.**

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 2 1)
                              (list 1 3))))

(define sym? (linalg/is-symmetric? A))

(list 'A A 'symmetric? sym?)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing #t]
<!-- BUILD: run; verify linalg/is-symmetric?; print result -->

**A non-symmetric matrix.**

```scheme
(define B (matrix/make (list (list 1 2)
                              (list 3 4))))

(define sym? (linalg/is-symmetric? B))

(list 'B B 'symmetric? sym?)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing #f]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**Eigenvalues of a symmetric matrix are real.**

```scheme
(define S (matrix/make (list (list 5 2 0)
                              (list 2 5 0)
                              (list 0 0 3))))

(define evals (linalg/eigenvalues S))

(list 'S S 'eigenvalues evals)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing three real eigenvalues]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**Eigenvectors of a symmetric matrix from different eigenvalues are orthogonal.**

```scheme
(define S (matrix/make (list (list 3 1)
                              (list 1 3))))

(define evecs (linalg/eigenvectors S))

;; Conceptually, if evecs = [v1 v2], then v1 · v2 = 0
(list 'S S 'eigenvectors evecs)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing eigenvectors (conceptual note that they're orthogonal)]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**Diagonalization of a symmetric 2×2 matrix** — conceptual, using eigenvalues and eigenvectors.

```scheme
(define S (matrix/make (list (list 4 2)
                              (list 2 1))))

(define evals (linalg/eigenvalues S))
(define evecs (linalg/eigenvectors S))

(list 'S S 'eigenvalues evals 'eigenvectors evecs)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing the decomposition components]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

