## Topic 9 — Singular Value Decomposition (SVD)

**Singular Value Decomposition** (SVD) is the ultimate matrix factorization. Every matrix A (even non-square, even rank-deficient) can be written as **A = UΣVᵀ**, where U and V are orthogonal and Σ is diagonal with nonnegative entries (the **singular values**). SVD generalizes eigendecomposition to any matrix, reveals the rank, provides the best low-rank approximation, and is the engine behind principal component analysis, image compression, recommender systems, and pseudoinverses.

**SVD of a 2×2 matrix.**

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 3 2)
                              (list 2 3))))

(define svd-result (linalg/svd A))

(list 'A A 'SVD svd-result)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing the SVD components (U, Σ, Vᵀ or a tagged structure)]
<!-- BUILD: run; verify linalg/svd; print result -->

**SVD of a rectangular (tall) matrix.**

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 0)
                              (list 0 1)
                              (list 1 1))))

(define svd-result (linalg/svd A))

svd-result
```
[VISUAL: text output showing the SVD of a 3×2 matrix]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**Singular values of a diagonal matrix** are the absolute values of the diagonal entries.

```scheme
(define D (matrix/make (list (list 5 0)
                              (list 0 -3))))

(define svd-result (linalg/svd D))

svd-result
```
[VISUAL: text output showing singular values [5, 3]]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**SVD of a rank-1 matrix** (outer product of two vectors).

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 2 4)
                              (list 1 2))))

(define svd-result (linalg/svd A))

svd-result
```
[VISUAL: text output showing one large singular value and one near-zero]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**SVD reveals the rank** — the number of nonzero singular values.

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 2 3)
                              (list 2 4 6))))

(define svd-result (linalg/svd A))
(define rank (linalg/rank A))

(list 'A A 'SVD svd-result 'rank rank)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing SVD and rank = 1]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

