## Topic 11 — Determinant, Invertibility, and Matrix Properties

The **determinant** of a square matrix measures the signed volume of the parallelepiped spanned by its column vectors. If det(A) = 0, the matrix is **singular** (not invertible) — it squashes space to lower dimension. Properties: det(AB) = det(A)det(B), det(Aᵀ) = det(A), det(A⁻¹) = 1/det(A).

**Determinant of a 2×2 matrix** (ad - bc).

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 3 5)
                              (list 2 4))))

(define det (matrix/determinant A))

(list 'A A 'determinant det)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing det = 2]
<!-- BUILD: run; verify matrix/determinant; print result -->

**Determinant of a 3×3 matrix** (expansion by minors or LU).

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 2 3)
                              (list 0 1 4)
                              (list 5 6 0))))

(define det (matrix/determinant A))

(list 'A A 'determinant det)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing det = 1]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**Determinant of the identity matrix is 1.**

```scheme
(define I (matrix/identity 3))

(define det (matrix/determinant I))

(list 'I I 'determinant det)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing det = 1]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**Determinant of a singular matrix is 0.**

```scheme
(define S (matrix/make (list (list 1 2)
                              (list 2 4))))

(define det (matrix/determinant S))

(list 'S S 'determinant det)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing det = 0]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**Check if a matrix is invertible.**

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 4 7)
                              (list 2 6))))

(define inv? (linalg/is-invertible? A))

(list 'A A 'invertible? inv?)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing #t]
<!-- BUILD: run; verify linalg/is-invertible?; print result -->

**A singular matrix is not invertible.**

```scheme
(define S (matrix/make (list (list 1 2)
                              (list 2 4))))

(define inv? (linalg/is-invertible? S))

(list 'S S 'invertible? inv?)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing #f]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**Determinant product rule:** det(AB) = det(A)det(B).

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 2 0)
                              (list 0 3))))
(define B (matrix/make (list (list 1 4)
                              (list 0 2))))

(define detA (matrix/determinant A))
(define detB (matrix/determinant B))
(define AB (matrix/* A B))
(define detAB (matrix/determinant AB))

(list 'det-A detA 'det-B detB 'det-AB detAB 'product (* detA detB))
```
[VISUAL: text output verifying det(AB) = det(A)*det(B)]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**Determinant of transpose:** det(Aᵀ) = det(A).

```scheme
(define A (matrix/make (list (list 1 2)
                              (list 3 4))))

(define detA (matrix/determinant A))
(define At (matrix/transpose A))
(define detAt (matrix/determinant At))

(list 'det-A detA 'det-At detAt 'equal? (= detA detAt))
```
[VISUAL: text output showing the determinants are equal]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

