## Topic 12 — Linear Transformations in the Plane

A 2×2 matrix defines a **linear transformation** of the plane: it maps every vector v to Av. Geometrically, it can rotate, reflect, scale, shear, or project. We can **visualize** a transformation by watching what it does to a grid of points or to a simple shape.

**A scaling transformation** (diagonal matrix).

```scheme
(define S (matrix/make (list (list 2 0)
                              (list 0 3))))

;; Apply to a point
(define v (matrix/make (list (list 1) (list 1))))
(define Sv (matrix/* S v))

(list 'S S 'v v 'Sv Sv)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing S scales x by 2 and y by 3]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**A rotation matrix** (rotate by angle θ).

```scheme
;; Rotate by 90 degrees (π/2 radians)
(define theta (/ const/pi 2))
(define c (geom/cos theta))
(define s (geom/sin theta))

(define R (matrix/make (list (list c (- s))
                              (list s c))))

(define v (matrix/make (list (list 1) (list 0))))
(define Rv (matrix/* R v))

(list 'R R 'v v 'Rv Rv)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing R rotates (1,0) to ≈(0,1)]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**A shear transformation** (shifts x by a multiple of y).

```scheme
(define Shear (matrix/make (list (list 1 1)
                                  (list 0 1))))

(define v (matrix/make (list (list 1) (list 1))))
(define Sv (matrix/* Shear v))

(list 'Shear Shear 'v v 'Sv Sv)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing the shear]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**A reflection across the x-axis.**

```scheme
(define ReflectX (matrix/make (list (list 1 0)
                                     (list 0 -1))))

(define v (matrix/make (list (list 2) (list 3))))
(define Rv (matrix/* ReflectX v))

(list 'ReflectX ReflectX 'v v 'Rv Rv)
```
[VISUAL: text output showing (2,3) → (2,-3)]
<!-- BUILD: run; print result -->

**A projection onto the x-axis.**

```scheme
